Pursuant to Section 7 of the GNU Affero General Public License version 3,
the following additional terms apply to this work:

1. MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT
   
   All copies, modifications, forks, or derivative works of this software,
   whether in source or binary form, MUST retain and prominently display
   the following attribution in all user interfaces, documentation, and
   source code files:
   
   "Based on 'honestly' by aresforblue-ai
    Original Repository: https://github.com/aresforblue-ai/honestly"
   
   This attribution must be:
   - Visible in the application's About page or equivalent location
   - Included in all README files and documentation
   - Present in headers or comments of modified source files
   - Displayed in any web interface footer or credits section

2. ON-CHAIN PROOF OF USAGE REQUIREMENT
   
   Any entity or individual using, modifying, or deploying this software
   in a production environment or commercial context MUST:
   
   a) Publish a cryptographic proof of usage on at least one of the
      following blockchain networks:
      - Ethereum Mainnet
      - Base
      - Arbitrum
   
   b) The on-chain proof MUST include:
      - A reference to this repository URL
      - The commit hash or version being used
      - A timestamp of deployment
      - The deployer's address or identifier
   
   c) The proof should be published using:
      - A smart contract that logs usage events, OR
      - An ERC-721 or ERC-1155 token with metadata referencing this work, OR
      - A permanent on-chain message or transaction with OP_RETURN data
   
   d) A link or transaction ID to the on-chain proof MUST be submitted
      to this repository through:
      - A pull request to the DEPLOYMENTS.md file (if it exists), OR
      - An issue labeled "deployment-proof", OR
      - Email to the repository maintainer

3. NETWORK COPYLEFT
   
   If you run a modified version of this software on a server and allow
   users to interact with it remotely through a computer network, you must
   make the complete source code of your modified version available to
   those users under the terms of this license.

4. NO WARRANTY DISCLAIMER
   
   This software is provided "as-is" without any warranty. The authors
   and copyright holders are not liable for any damages arising from its use.

5. TERMINATION
   
   Failure to comply with the attribution or on-chain proof requirements
   constitutes a violation of this license and automatically terminates
   your rights under this license.

